cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category cs.CL (Computation and Language) because it deals with natural language processing and specifically focuses on predicting coordination boundaries in sentences. The use of neural networks also suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the use of LSTM networks indicates that it could belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the mention of the PTB and Genia corpus suggests that it could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) as these are commonly used datasets in natural language processing research.
